
[1]arian

   A'RIAN, a. Pertaining to Arius, a presbyter of the church of
   Alexandria, in the fourth century; or to his doctrines.

   A'RIAN, n. One who adheres to the doctrines of Arius, who held Christ
   to be a created being, inferior to God the father in nature and
   dignity, though the first and noblest of all created beings; and also
   that the Holy Spirit is not God, but created by the power of the Son.
